# <package / app name>

<One line: what this surface is.>

## Applicable ADRs

- ADR-001 Clean Architecture · ADR-002 Package-by-component · ADR-003 Dependency Injection ·
  ADR-004 Frontend state · ADR-005 Boundary enforcement
- <plus any surface-specific ADRs>

## Structure

- Package-by-component: capabilities as folders under `src/<component>/`, each fronted by `index.ts`.
- Clean layers nest **inside** a component: `domain/` `application/` `infrastructure/` `presentation/`.
- Shared technical modules under `src/shared/` (each its own facade); shared UI/kit is its own package.

## Layer rules

- Dependencies point inward only. Interfaces live in `application/` with the use cases; `domain/` =
  entities + value objects + errors.
- Controllers/handlers are thin; use cases never see delivery types.

## DI

- Inversify; inject interfaces only; `Thing` / `<Qualifier>Thing` naming; tokens in `types.ts`
  (`TYPES`). Rebind to mocks in tests.
- <frontend only> Container wires logic; the query client + Zustand stores stay idiomatic (not in the
  container); reach the container via `useInjection`.

## State  <frontend only>

- Server → TanStack Query · shared client → Zustand · local → `useState`. Never mirror server state
  into Zustand.

## Enforcement

- `index.ts` facades + `eslint-plugin-boundaries`. Don't import past a component's facade.

